CommonFields.Title: Morphology, thermal, and rheological behavior of nylon 11/multi-walled carbon nanotube nanocomposites prepared by melt compounding
Author: Huang, Shu
Wang, Min
Liu, Tianxi
Zhang, Wei-De
Tjiu, Wuiwui Chauhari
He, Chaobin
Lu, Xuehong
CommonFields.Location: Key Laboratory of Molecular Engineering of Polymers of Ministry of Education, Department of Macromolecular Science, Laboratory of Advanced, Materials, Fudan University, Shanghai 200433, China

Mixing.Description: Selective reduction at 1000°C in a methane-hydrogen (18% CH4) atmosphere of a solid solution of a transition metal oxide led to the formation of small diameter CNTs with one to three walls.
After the reaction, the unreacted catalytic particles were dissolved in concentrated nitric acid and CNTs were recovered.

ChooseParameter.Other: CNT powder was filtered and washed with deionized water for at least five times.

Mixing.Description: MWNTs were further refluxed in 2.6 M nitric acid in order to increase more carboxylic and hydroxyl groups on the surface of the MWNTs.

Drying-Evaporation.Description: As polyamides are very easy to absorb moisture, prior to compounding all the samples were dried in vacuum oven at 80°C for 24 h in order to remove the absorbed water.

Scanning_Electron_Microscopy.Description: The dispersion morphology of the composites was observed for the cryo-fractured surfaces with an SEM at an accelerating voltage of 30 kV after coating the samples with a thin layer of gold.

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Equipment: dynamic mechanical analyzer from TA Instruments
Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Description: DMA was performed on the samples of 30 x 10 x 0.5 mm in size under tension film mode in a temperature range of -134-150°C at a frequency of 1 Hz and heating rate of 3°C/min.

Thermogravimetric_Analysis.Description: Thermogravimetric analysis was performed from 50 to 600°C at a heating rate of 20°C/min by using a Shimadzu TG-60H under nitrogen atmosphere.

Rheometery.Description: Melt rheological properties of neat PA11 and PA11/MWNT composites were measured on a strain-controlled rheometer over a temperature range of 190–210°C. Small-amplitude oscillatory shear measurements were performed using parallel-plate geometry with the plate diameter of 25 mm and the plate gap setting of 1.0 mm.

SampleSize.description: DMA sample size: 30 mm x 10 mm
